UNITED STATES of America v. NAVAJO FREIGHT LINES, INC. No. 7246. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. May 28, 1963. Alan S. Rosenthal and Terence N. Doyle, Attys., Dept, of Justice, Washington, D. C., and Arthur L. Fine, Asst. U. S. Atty., Denver, Colo., for appellant. Barry & Boyle, Denver, Colo., for ap-pellee.

Before PICKETT and BREITEN-STEIN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed May 28, 1963, pursuant to stipulation of the parties. 186 F.Supp. 377.
